Nominees - Best Actor Colin Firth  
2011-01-28 09:48:51 GMT
Colin Firth is widely considered the frontrunner for the Best Actor statue thanks to his knock-down performance in The King's Speech. While this is Firth's second nomination in the category in two consecutive years, he was never nominated for an Oscar before A Single Man put him on the Academy's radar.
